ps aux : 

    a : DISPLAY ALL PROCESSES INCLUDING ALL USERS
    u : DISPLAY MORE DETAILS ABOUT PROCESSES
    x : LIST ALL PROCESSES WITHOUT TTY

        USER : Effective user
        PID : PROCESS ID
        %CPU : CPU Time used Divided by Time Process running
        %MEM : Ratio of Process Resident Set Size to Physical Memory 
        VSZ : Virtual Memory Usage of Whole Process
        RSS : Resident Set Size, Non Swapped Physical Memory
        TTY : CONTROLLING TERMINAL ASSOCIATED WITH PROCESS
        STAT : PROCESS STATUS CODE
        START : Start Time of Process
        TIME : TOTAL CPU USAGE TIME
        CMD : NAME OF EXECUTABLE OR COMMAND


top : REAL TIME INFO OF PROCESS DEFUALT REFRESH EVERY 10 SECONDS 


SIGNALS : 

    SIGHUP or hup or 1: Hangup

    SIGINT or int or 2: Interrupt

    SIGKILL or kill or 9: Kill

    SIGSEGV or segv or 11: Segmentation fault

    SIGTERM or term or 15: Software termination

    SIGSTOP or stop: Stop


KILL COMMAND : 
    kill PID 
    kill -9 PID


NICENESS MORE NEGATIVE MORE PRIORITY : 
    
    SET PRIORITY FOR NEW COMMAND to Nth : nice -n N Command

    SET PRIORITY FOR EXISTING PROCESS : renice N -p PID

PROCESS INFO FILE : ls /proc


JOB CONTROL : 

    SENDING NEW JOB TO BACKGROUND : commands &

    VIEW JOBS : jobs

    SENDING EXISTING JOB TO BACKGROUND : bg

    BACKGROUND TO FOREGROUND : fg jobID

    KILL BACKGROUND JOBS : kill jobID



